cs.RO, cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with controlling the workspace of a mobile robot.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper focuses on ensuring human-aware navigation in shared spaces.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the paper uses an RGB-D camera for the human-robot interface.
- cs.GR (Graphics) is relevant as the paper employs an augmented reality application for defining virtual borders.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper evaluates the system with non-expert users and compares it with other baseline methods.
